posts.title: Hey ChatGPT - Do H-1B employers have to pay Federal Unemployment Tax?
posts.content:
1. Federal Unemployment Tax (FUTA): FUTA is paid by the employer and is not withheld from the employee's wages, regardless of whether the employee is a U.S. citizen or on an H-1B visa.

However, there’s a significant nuance: H-1B workers are not subject to FUTA. The IRS generally does not require employers to pay FUTA on H-1B workers because their work visa status exempts them from the FUTA tax. So, employers do not pay FUTA taxes on H-1B employees.
